==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foreman
<hw>Fore"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Foremen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>The first or chief
man</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The chief man of a jury, who acts as
their speaker.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The chief of a set of hands
employed in a shop, or on works of any kind, who superintends the rest;
an overseer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>foremanship</ent>⟦br⟧
